margin-top:7px;margin-bottom:3px">授業形態</div></td><td width="50" align="center"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">講義</div></td></tr><tr><td width="100" align="center" bgcolor="lightsteelblue"><div style="margin-top:7px;margin-bottom:3px">授業実施方法</div></td><td colspan=3 width="450" align="left"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">&nbsp;&nbsp&#9745対面&nbsp;&nbsp&#9744オンデマンド&nbsp;&nbsp&#9744同時双方向<br></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan="4" width="580"><div style="margin:10px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">ディプロマ・ポリシーとの対応</div><div style="margin:10px">&#9744&nbsp1.&nbsp人間，文化，社会を理解し，それらを技術的観点から考察する能力と技術を新しい生活につなぐ強い使命感・責任感，高い倫理観<br>&#9744&nbsp2.&nbsp現象の理解・操作のための数理的基礎知識と科学的素養<br>&#9745&nbsp3.&nbsp国内外の人々と対話できるコミュニケーション力と論理的思考力<br>&#9744&nbsp4.&nbsp（高度工学教育課程のみ）基幹となる専門分野の基盤的な知識・技術とこれによって課題を解決する能力，新たな知識・技術を習得する能力<br>&#9744&nbsp4.&nbsp（創造工学教育課程のみ）基幹となる専門分野の基礎知識と他の分野の知識・技術を関連づけ多面的に見ることで新たな価値を創出する能力<br></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan="4" width="580"><div style="margin:10px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">授業の目的・達成目標</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>【授業の目的】</p>
<p>This course emphasizes communicative evaluation and analysis. The overall goal of the course is to improve student ability to understand and produce extended discourse in English, especially in reading and writing contexts. Academic English vocabulary, recognizing and summarizing key points, critical thinking skills, and logical argumentation based on examples and evidence will be emphasized.</p>
<p>【達成目標】</p>
<p>Students will</p>
<p>・acquire greater skills in reading articles in English and knowledge about a variety of current topics,</p>
<p>・enlarge their academic vocabulary and improve their ability to understand the grammatical structure of sentences and paragraphs, and</p>
<p>・gain experience in writing their opinion on current topics.</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">授業計画</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>初回授業時に具体的な授業の方法・計画を、Moodleで詳細に説明するので、よく読んで確認すること。</p>
<p>Weeks 1, 2, and 3: Unit 7 Energy Solutions</p>
<p>            - 7A Powering the Planet - Identifying Pros and Cons (2)</p>
<p>            - 7B City of the Future? - Identifying an Author's Opinion </p>
<p>            - Review Quiz</p>
<p>            - Video - Wave Power </p>
<p>Weeks 4, 5, and 6: Unit 8 Epic Engineering</p>
<p>            - 8A China's Grand Canal - Understanding Vocabulary: Compound Words</p>
<p>            - 8B Highway of Dreams - Inferring Information</p>
<p>            - Review Quiz</p>
<p>            - Video - Building a Rain Forest</p>
<p>Week 7: Work Shop - Relationship Between Talking and Singing</p>
<p>Weeks 8, 9, and 10: Unit 9 High-Tech Solutions</p>
<p>            - 9A The Power of Virtual Reality - Applying Information from Text</p>
<p>            - 9B High-Flying Helpers - Recognizing Text Coherence </p>
<p>            - Review Quiz</p>
<p>            - Video - Drone Delivery</p>
<p>Week 11, 12, and 13: Unit 10 All in the Mind</p>
<p>            - 10A What's on Your Mind? - Identifying Text Organization</p>
<p>            - 10B Inside Animal Minds - Recognizing Lexical Cohesion</p>
<p>            - Review Quiz</p>
<p>            - Video - Brain Power</p>
<p> Week 14 and 15: Unit 11 Visual Pioneers</p>
<p>            - 11A Van Gogh's World - Inferring Information (2)</p>
<p>            - 11B Seeing the Light - Recognizing Lexical Cohesion (2)</p>
<p>            - Review Quiz</p>
<p>            - Video - The Genius of Picasso</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Contents and the schedule may change according to the level of students.</p>
<p> </p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">成績評価の方法</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>Vocabulary Checking: 30%, Note-taking: 40%, Assignments: 30%</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">成績評価の基準</div><div style="margin:10px">秀　 達成目標を超えた成果を上げている　100点～90点<br>優　 達成目標に十分達している　　　　　89点～80点<br>良　 達成目標に達している　　　　　　　79点～70点<br>可　 達成目標に概ね達している　　　　　69点～60点<br>不可 達成目標に達していない　　　　　　59点以下<br><p>The teacher will explain the grading system in class. Based on a maximum score of 100, grades will be awarded as follows:</p>
<p>S (Excellent) 90-100</p>
<p>A (Very good) 80-90</p>
<p>B (Good) 70-80</p>
<p>C (Pass) 60-70</p>
<p>D (Fail) Below 60.</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">事前・事後学修等の指示及び履修にあたっての注意事項</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>Self Preparation: Check the words in the textbook while answering the questions.(120 min.)</p>
<p>Review: Make note in English in your notebook to make sure you understand the passage. (120 min.)</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">教科書</div><div style="margin:10px">Reading Explorer 3 Third Edition, National Geographic Learning<br></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">参考書</div><div style="margin:10px"></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">オフィスアワー</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>By appointment.</p>
